body:
@jhoneill Thank you very much for the XML file, I will definitely use this with some changes and in my guide as well.

But my point was exactly about the fact that the default format sucks and could be improved.

I have 68 columns btw not 40, which is a bit small but generally adequate.

@dkaszews  no apology needed from my side, I talk the same way to people :-) But the powers-that-be like to keep the atmosphere welcoming.   

I hadn't even allowed for ubuntu looking different, and it depends on the example used. (And how much more there is to process after the last item). 

@rkitover  I'm a bit conditioned to what Update-FormatData and XML files do so I'd be interested to see the prototype of what some extra functionality might look like.
